description: The <input type="text"> HTML element allows the user to enter information into a form. By default, an <input> element is a text input.
description_html: The <input type="text"> HTML element allows the user to enter information into a form. By default, an <input> element is a text input.
name: <input>

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 89, manipulating the content of <input> elements using Document.execCommand() commands requires workarounds (see bug 1220696).

firefox_android.notes: Before Firefox for Android 89, manipulating the content of <input> elements using Document.execCommand() commands requires workarounds (see bug 1220696).
